{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Cd2qNesfr11ScrVV5pmTcG","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.coffeeshop.barista.health;\n     2→\n     3→import org.eclipse.microprofile.health.HealthCheck;\n     4→import org.eclipse.microprofile.health.HealthCheckResponse;\n     5→import org.eclipse.microprofile.health.Readiness;\n     6→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     7→\n     8→@Readiness\n     9→@ApplicationScoped\n    10→public class BasicHealth implements HealthCheck {\n    11→    @Override\n    12→    public HealthCheckResponse call() {\n    13→        return HealthCheckResponse.up(\"barista-service\");\n    14→    }\n    15→}\n    16→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7f83cc93-22fd-4116-9105-e05599539b19","uuid":"0d2b3c66-800d-49bc-9d0f-163bacb1ce43"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_0113Awh4LM8gDFvBd2SbKvj6","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.coffeeshop.barista.messaging;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     4→import jakarta.json.bind.Jsonb;\n     5→import jakarta.json.bind.JsonbBuilder;\n     6→import org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.Incoming;\n     7→import org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.Outgoing;\n     8→import org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.Message;\n     9→\n    10→import java.util.HashMap;\n    11→import java.util.Map;\n    12→\n    13→@ApplicationScoped\n    14→public class BaristaConsumer {\n    15→\n    16→    private final Jsonb jsonb = JsonbBuilder.create();\n    17→\n    18→    // Consumes commands from orders-service (topic: barista-commands)\n    19→    @Incoming(\"barista\")\n    20→    // Publishes order status updates (topic: order-updates)\n    21→    @Outgoing(\"order-updates\")\n    22→    public Message<String> makeCoffee(String orderJson) {\n    23→        try {\n    24→            System.out.println(\"[barista] received: \" + orderJson);\n    25→            // Parse whatever orders-service sent (JSON String)\n    26→            Map<String, Object> in = jsonb.fromJson(orderJson, Map.class);\n    27→\n    28→            // Carry through orderId if present (original Quarkus did this)\n    29→            Object orderId = in.get(\"orderId\");\n    30→\n    31→            Map<String, Object> out = new HashMap<>();\n    32→            if (orderId != null) {\n    33→                out.put(\"orderId\", orderId);\n    34→            }\n    35→            out.put(\"status\", \"READY\");\n    36→            out.put(\"from\", \"barista\");\n    37→\n    38→            // Produce clean JSON (no backslashes)\n    39→            return Message.of(jsonb.toJson(out));\n    40→\n    41→        } catch (Exception e) {\n    42→            System.err.println(\"[barista] parse/update error: \" + e + \" payload=\" + orderJson);\n    43→            // Let the framework nack and surface the error rather than emitting malformed JSON\n    44→            throw e;\n    45→        }\n    46→    }\n    47→}\n    48→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7f83cc93-22fd-4116-9105-e05599539b19","uuid":"b6e461bb-7bca-41ad-823d-d233bb5ade6c"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01YDKJxG4mHJ59Fgkew1575T","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→\n     2→app.name=barista-service\n     3→# Broker\n     4→mp.messaging.connector.liberty-kafka.bootstrap.servers=${KAFKA_BOOTSTRAP}\n     5→\n     6→# --- incoming: barista commands ---\n     7→mp.messaging.incoming.barista.connector=liberty-kafka\n     8→mp.messaging.incoming.barista.topic=barista-commands\n     9→mp.messaging.incoming.barista.key.deserializer=org.apache.kafka.common.serialization.StringDeserializer\n    10→mp.messaging.incoming.barista.value.deserializer=org.apache.kafka.common.serialization.StringDeserializer\n    11→# nice for dev: start at latest or earliest depending on your preference\n    12→mp.messaging.incoming.barista.auto.offset.reset=latest\n    13→mp.messaging.incoming.barista.group.id=barista-service-dev\n    14→\n    15→# --- outgoing: updates -> order-updates topic ---\n    16→mp.messaging.outgoing.order-updates.connector=liberty-kafka\n    17→mp.messaging.outgoing.order-updates.topic=order-updates\n    18→mp.messaging.outgoing.order-updates.key.serializer=org.apache.kafka.common.serialization.StringSerializer\n    19→mp.messaging.outgoing.order-updates.value.serializer=org.apache.kafka.common.serialization.StringSerializer\n    20→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7f83cc93-22fd-4116-9105-e05599539b19","uuid":"027084e8-759c-490d-b47e-1b89b6a4944f"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01ARiprD7BDj6KBeNH5EsFfU","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<server>\n     2→  <featureManager>\n     3→    <!-- was: <feature>jakartaee-10.0</feature> -->\n     4→    <feature>webProfile-10.0</feature>\n     5→    <feature>mpConfig-3.1</feature>\n     6→    <feature>mpHealth-4.0</feature>\n     7→    <feature>mpOpenAPI-3.1</feature>\n     8→    <feature>mpMetrics-5.1</feature>\n     9→    <feature>mpRestClient-3.0</feature>\n    10→    <feature>mpReactiveMessaging-3.0</feature>\n    11→    <feature>mpJwt-2.1</feature>\n    12→  </featureManager>\n    13→\n    14→  <httpEndpoint id=\"defaultHttpEndpoint\" host=\"*\" httpPort=\"9081\" httpsPort=\"9444\"/>\n    15→\n    16→   <!-- Minimal user registry to satisfy security-enabled features in dev -->\n    17→  <basicRegistry id=\"basic\" realm=\"defaultRealm\">\n    18→    <user name=\"admin\" password=\"adminpwd\"/>\n    19→  </basicRegistry>\n    20→\n    21→  <!-- JDBC config -->\n    22→  <library id=\"jdbcLib\">\n    23→    <fileset dir=\"${server.config.dir}/lib/global/\" includes=\"*.jar\"/>\n    24→  </library>\n    25→\n    26→  <dataSource id=\"ordersDS\" jndiName=\"jdbc/ordersDS\">\n    27→    <jdbcDriver libraryRef=\"jdbcLib\"/>\n    28→    <properties databaseName=\"${env.DB_NAME}\" user=\"${env.DB_USER}\" password=\"${env.DB_PASS}\" serverName=\"${env.DB_HOST}\" portNumber=\"${env.DB_PORT}\"/>\n    29→  </dataSource>\n    30→\n    31→</server>\n    32→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7f83cc93-22fd-4116-9105-e05599539b19","uuid":"6479082d-bf04-4e4d-8175-33a6e2f62836"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01QHWqWJSmd2canYNZpFEGAu","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→FROM maven:3.9.12-ibm-semeru-21-noble\n     2→\n     3→USER root\n     4→# install uv\n     5→RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends curl python3-venv python3-full     && curl -LsSf https://astral.sh/uv/install.sh | sh\n     6→\n     7→ENV PATH=\"/root/.local/bin:$PATH\"\n     8→\n     9→# Shared browsers path so Chromium is cached once\n    10→ENV PLAYWRIGHT_BROWSERS_PATH=/ms-playwright\n    11→RUN mkdir -p /ms-playwright && chmod 755 /ms-playwright\n    12→\n    13→# create venv and install\n    14→RUN uv venv /opt/venv     && uv pip install --python /opt/venv/bin/python playwright==1.47.0 pytest\n    15→\n    16→ENV PATH=\"/opt/venv/bin:$PATH\"\n    17→RUN playwright install --with-deps chromium\n    18→\n    19→# Set working directory\n    20→WORKDIR /app\n    21→\n    22→# Copy all the assets\n    23→COPY . .\n    24→\n    25→RUN if [ -f mvnw ]; then chmod +x mvnw; fi && if [ -f smoke.py ]; then chmod +x smoke.py; fi\n    26→\n    27→CMD [ \"mvn\", \"clean\", \"liberty:run\" ]\n    28→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7f83cc93-22fd-4116-9105-e05599539b19","uuid":"96ca9f7e-b039-4ead-a7f5-5628e739d8eb"}
