{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01H3fgvWtWyVbPDXzK2jEPQa","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.coffeeshop.kitchen.health;\n     2→\n     3→import org.eclipse.microprofile.health.HealthCheck;\n     4→import org.eclipse.microprofile.health.HealthCheckResponse;\n     5→import org.eclipse.microprofile.health.Readiness;\n     6→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     7→\n     8→@Readiness\n     9→@ApplicationScoped\n    10→public class BasicHealth implements HealthCheck {\n    11→    @Override\n    12→    public HealthCheckResponse call() {\n    13→        return HealthCheckResponse.up(\"kitchen-service\");\n    14→    }\n    15→}\n    16→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7f83cc93-22fd-4116-9105-e05599539b19","uuid":"6878b4ab-40ec-42ed-acc0-c22e4bb4b0ad"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01WTsoW6QLVspCsw1ydnfKiV","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.coffeeshop.kitchen.messaging;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     4→import org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.Incoming;\n     5→import org.eclipse.microprofile.reactive.messaging.Outgoing;\n     6→\n     7→import jakarta.json.Json;\n     8→import jakarta.json.JsonObject;\n     9→\n    10→import java.io.StringReader;\n    11→\n    12→@ApplicationScoped\n    13→public class KitchenConsumer {\n    14→\n    15→    @Incoming(\"kitchen\")          // channel that reads topic: kitchen-commands\n    16→    @Outgoing(\"order-updates\")    // channel that writes topic: order-updates\n    17→    public String cookFood(String orderJson) {\n    18→        System.out.println(\"[kitchen] received: \" + orderJson);\n    19→        // Parse the incoming order (so we can carry orderId across)\n    20→        JsonObject in = Json.createReader(new StringReader(orderJson)).readObject();\n    21→\n    22→        // If original event had orderId, propagate it\n    23→        JsonObject out = Json.createObjectBuilder()\n    24→                .add(\"status\", \"READY\")\n    25→                .add(\"from\", \"kitchen\")\n    26→                .add(\"orderId\", in.containsKey(\"orderId\") ? in.getJsonNumber(\"orderId\").longValue() : -1)\n    27→                .build();\n    28→\n    29→        // This returns a real JSON object string: {\"status\":\"READY\",\"from\":\"kitchen\",\"orderId\":...}\n    30→        return out.toString();\n    31→    }\n    32→}\n    33→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7f83cc93-22fd-4116-9105-e05599539b19","uuid":"07ae28e4-004b-422d-8195-6118d05ee9cb"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01XfDTFxJQEfHqjLKciYQxRi","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→mp.messaging.connector.liberty-kafka.bootstrap.servers=${KAFKA_BOOTSTRAP}\n     2→mp.messaging.incoming.kitchen.connector=liberty-kafka\n     3→mp.messaging.incoming.kitchen.topic=kitchen-commands\n     4→mp.messaging.incoming.kitchen.group.id=kitchen-service\n     5→mp.messaging.incoming.kitchen.key.deserializer=org.apache.kafka.common.serialization.StringDeserializer\n     6→mp.messaging.incoming.kitchen.value.deserializer=org.apache.kafka.common.serialization.StringDeserializer\n     7→mp.messaging.outgoing.order-updates.connector=liberty-kafka\n     8→mp.messaging.outgoing.order-updates.topic=order-updates\n     9→mp.messaging.outgoing.order-updates.key.serializer=org.apache.kafka.common.serialization.StringSerializer\n    10→mp.messaging.outgoing.order-updates.value.serializer=org.apache.kafka.common.serialization.StringSerializer\n    11→app.name=kitchen-service\n    12→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7f83cc93-22fd-4116-9105-e05599539b19","uuid":"46f422f5-b00c-403e-b391-3078313f6235"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_014vsHKFcD6QenRaPyTE1Cst","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<server>\n     2→  <featureManager>\n     3→    <!-- was: <feature>jakartaee-10.0</feature> -->\n     4→    <feature>webProfile-10.0</feature>\n     5→    <feature>mpConfig-3.1</feature>\n     6→    <feature>mpHealth-4.0</feature>\n     7→    <feature>mpOpenAPI-3.1</feature>\n     8→    <feature>mpMetrics-5.1</feature>\n     9→    <feature>mpRestClient-3.0</feature>\n    10→    <feature>mpReactiveMessaging-3.0</feature>\n    11→    <feature>mpJwt-2.1</feature>\n    12→  </featureManager>\n    13→\n    14→  <httpEndpoint id=\"defaultHttpEndpoint\" host=\"*\" httpPort=\"9082\" httpsPort=\"9445\"/>\n    15→\n    16→  <!-- Minimal user registry to satisfy security-enabled features in dev -->\n    17→  <basicRegistry id=\"basic\" realm=\"defaultRealm\">\n    18→    <user name=\"admin\" password=\"adminpwd\"/>\n    19→  </basicRegistry>\n    20→  <!-- JDBC config -->\n    21→  <library id=\"jdbcLib\">\n    22→    <fileset dir=\"${server.config.dir}/lib/global/\" includes=\"*.jar\"/>\n    23→  </library>\n    24→\n    25→  <dataSource id=\"ordersDS\" jndiName=\"jdbc/ordersDS\">\n    26→    <jdbcDriver libraryRef=\"jdbcLib\"/>\n    27→    <properties databaseName=\"${env.DB_NAME}\" user=\"${env.DB_USER}\" password=\"${env.DB_PASS}\" serverName=\"${env.DB_HOST}\" portNumber=\"${env.DB_PORT}\"/>\n    28→  </dataSource>\n    29→\n    30→</server>\n    31→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7f83cc93-22fd-4116-9105-e05599539b19","uuid":"54c3fcb1-81e0-4c52-bf00-2cce052797ef"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01KidZ2DY9AE2NrE8b89Jba1","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→FROM maven:3.9.12-ibm-semeru-21-noble\n     2→\n     3→USER root\n     4→# install uv\n     5→RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends curl python3-venv python3-full     && curl -LsSf https://astral.sh/uv/install.sh | sh\n     6→\n     7→ENV PATH=\"/root/.local/bin:$PATH\"\n     8→\n     9→# Shared browsers path so Chromium is cached once\n    10→ENV PLAYWRIGHT_BROWSERS_PATH=/ms-playwright\n    11→RUN mkdir -p /ms-playwright && chmod 755 /ms-playwright\n    12→\n    13→# create venv and install\n    14→RUN uv venv /opt/venv     && uv pip install --python /opt/venv/bin/python playwright==1.47.0 pytest\n    15→\n    16→ENV PATH=\"/opt/venv/bin:$PATH\"\n    17→RUN playwright install --with-deps chromium\n    18→\n    19→# Set working directory\n    20→WORKDIR /app\n    21→\n    22→# Copy all the assets\n    23→COPY . .\n    24→\n    25→RUN if [ -f mvnw ]; then chmod +x mvnw; fi && if [ -f smoke.py ]; then chmod +x smoke.py; fi\n    26→\n    27→CMD [ \"mvn\", \"clean\", \"liberty:run\" ]\n    28→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7f83cc93-22fd-4116-9105-e05599539b19","uuid":"9685923b-f8c0-4b83-a3be-acf057449fa3"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01FeA2RaabRQEaA8hKwtxUCh","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→FROM maven:3.9.12-ibm-semeru-21-noble\n     2→\n     3→USER root\n     4→# install uv\n     5→RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends curl python3-venv python3-full     && curl -LsSf https://astral.sh/uv/install.sh | sh\n     6→\n     7→ENV PATH=\"/root/.local/bin:$PATH\"\n     8→\n     9→# Shared browsers path so Chromium is cached once\n    10→ENV PLAYWRIGHT_BROWSERS_PATH=/ms-playwright\n    11→RUN mkdir -p /ms-playwright && chmod 755 /ms-playwright\n    12→\n    13→# create venv and install\n    14→RUN uv venv /opt/venv     && uv pip install --python /opt/venv/bin/python playwright==1.47.0 pytest\n    15→\n    16→ENV PATH=\"/opt/venv/bin:$PATH\"\n    17→RUN playwright install --with-deps chromium\n    18→\n    19→# Set working directory\n    20→WORKDIR /app\n    21→\n    22→# Copy all the assets\n    23→COPY . .\n    24→\n    25→RUN if [ -f mvnw ]; then chmod +x mvnw; fi && if [ -f smoke.py ]; then chmod +x smoke.py; fi\n    26→\n    27→CMD [ \"mvn\", \"clean\", \"liberty:run\" ]\n    28→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7f83cc93-22fd-4116-9105-e05599539b19","uuid":"50abbe68-e5d2-4a75-81f8-49752c5e4d6a"}
